1
00:00:02,916 --> 00:00:04,083
- I gotta ask, though.

2
00:00:04,166 --> 00:00:05,125
What made you wanna do this
in the first place?

3
00:00:05,208 --> 00:00:07,333
- I have a friend,

4
00:00:07,416 --> 00:00:09,666
and she won't stop
moping around.

5
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:10,916
It isn't good for her.

6
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,041
I just wanna kick her
in the butt a little bit.

7
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:16,000
<i>- In that moment,</i>

8
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:18,416
<i>that's when I felt like</i>
<i>something inside</i>

9
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:20,916
<i>of him might change.</i>

10
00:00:22,625 --> 00:00:26,458
<i>[COALAMODE.'S</i>
<i>"Nanairo Symphony"]</i>

11
00:00:26,541 --> 00:00:29,375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12
00:00:29,458 --> 00:00:32,416
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

13
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:39,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14
00:00:57,625 --> 00:01:04,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15
00:01:24,666 --> 00:01:31,583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,958
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17
00:01:57,041 --> 00:02:00,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18
00:02:00,625 --> 00:02:02,000
- Here goes.

19
00:02:02,083 --> 00:02:03,458
- Yeah.

20
00:02:03,541 --> 00:02:07,125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21
00:02:07,208 --> 00:02:09,125
- There she is!
- [gasps]

22
00:02:09,208 --> 00:02:10,666
- She's pretty cute, huh?
- [grumbles]

23
00:02:13,125 --> 00:02:14,041
[gasps]

24
00:02:14,125 --> 00:02:15,791
Arima?

25
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:17,166
- No way.
- Is that who I think it is?

26
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:20,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:22,958
- It's Kousei Arima.
- With Aiza's sister?

28
00:02:23,041 --> 00:02:23,958
- Aren't he and Aiza rivals?

29
00:02:24,041 --> 00:02:26,208
- I thought he retired
years ago.

30
00:02:26,291 --> 00:02:29,208
[applause]

31
00:02:29,291 --> 00:02:35,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32
00:02:37,208 --> 00:02:39,208
- Elohim, essaim.
Elohim, essaim.

33
00:02:39,291 --> 00:02:41,791
Most humbly I implore you.

34
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:42,958
- [gasps]

35
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:44,708
What does that mean?

36
00:02:44,791 --> 00:02:46,625
- Don't know.
Worth a try, right?

37
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,041
- [gasps, giggles]

38
00:02:48,125 --> 00:02:50,958
- [chuckles]

39
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:58,208
[piano music playing]

40
00:02:58,291 --> 00:03:05,500
♪ ♪

41
00:03:40,791 --> 00:03:47,708
♪ ♪

42
00:03:52,291 --> 00:03:54,041
<i>- [exhales]</i>
<i>Good.</i>

43
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:56,000
<i>It's going well so far.</i>

44
00:03:56,083 --> 00:04:03,125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:10,208
<i>- Nagi.</i>

46
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:11,291
<i>- You've gotta be kidding me.</i>

47
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:13,791
<i>In no time at all,</i>

48
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:16,958
<i>she's gotten way better.</i>

49
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:23,375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:26,416
<i>- Nagi,</i>
<i>knock 'em dead!</i>

51
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:30,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:34,083
<i>- My fingers were</i>
<i>so stiff before,</i>

53
00:04:34,166 --> 00:04:35,458
<i>but now they're moving.</i>

54
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:36,791
<i>The parts are clear.</i>

55
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:39,000
<i>Arima and I each have a job</i>
<i>to do.</i>

56
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:41,708
<i>All of that practice</i>
<i>is paying off.</i>

57
00:04:41,791 --> 00:04:48,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

58
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,791
<i>- It's hard to keep my focus.</i>

59
00:04:53,875 --> 00:04:56,208
<i>Every note I play,</i>
<i>I can hear it.</i>

60
00:04:56,291 --> 00:05:04,375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

61
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:09,333
<i>They're in my way.</i>

62
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:11,625
<i>If you won't help,</i>

63
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:12,916
<i>then go!</i>

64
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

65
00:05:14,583 --> 00:05:15,791
- [gasps]

66
00:05:15,875 --> 00:05:16,791
[all gasping]

67
00:05:16,875 --> 00:05:18,916
<i>Just now,</i>
<i>what happened?</i>

68
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,041
- [gasps]

69
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:22,791
<i>The sound,</i>
<i>it's different.</i>

70
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:25,208
<i>- Kousei?</i>

71
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:26,791
<i>- This came out of nowhere.</i>

72
00:05:26,875 --> 00:05:28,208
<i>What the heck are you doing?</i>

73
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:29,958
<i>You're supposed</i>
<i>to be helping me,</i>

74
00:05:30,041 --> 00:05:31,166
<i>not playing it</i>
<i>totally different</i>

75
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,083
<i>than every other time</i>
<i>we ran it!</i>

76
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,083
<i>You're a liar.</i>
<i>You're an idiot.</i>

77
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,291
<i>Or both.</i>

78
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:37,833
<i>I've never heard it</i>
<i>like this before.</i>

79
00:05:37,916 --> 00:05:39,041
<i>The rhythm,</i>

80
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:40,916
<i>the images crowding</i>
<i>into my heart,</i>

81
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,416
<i>everything!</i>

82
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,958
<i>This is an Arima</i>
<i>I couldn't have imagined.</i>

83
00:05:45,041 --> 00:05:48,416
<i>- The tempo is definitely</i>
<i>starting to pick up.</i>

84
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,458
<i>His base line is going</i>
<i>to drown out everything</i>

85
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:52,416
<i>If she's not careful.</i>

86
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,833
<i>- All right, Nagi.</i>
<i>Moment of truth.</i>

87
00:05:54,916 --> 00:05:58,166
<i>You gonna let Kousei boss</i>
<i>you around like this?</i>

88
00:05:58,250 --> 00:06:00,208
<i>Give him hell, kiddo.</i>

89
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:03,166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

90
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:05,333
<i>- So be it!</i>

91
00:06:05,416 --> 00:06:07,416
- [grunts]

92
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:14,666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

93
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:37,333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

94
00:06:37,416 --> 00:06:40,000
<i>- Nagi!</i>

95
00:06:40,083 --> 00:06:41,250
<i>- She's keeping up!</i>

96
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:42,750
<i>- Unreal.</i>

97
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,750
<i>- Aiza's kid sister's</i>
<i>holding her own.</i>

98
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:46,416
<i>- He's not going easy on her,</i>

99
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:48,791
<i>and she's still matching him</i>
<i>note for note.</i>

100
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,541
<i>Was she always this good?</i>

101
00:06:50,625 --> 00:06:56,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

102
00:07:08,708 --> 00:07:10,916
<i>- That a girl, Nagi.</i>

103
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
<i>You're the star</i>
<i>of that damn stage.</i>

104
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:16,416
<i>Make sure he knows it.</i>

105
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:23,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

106
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:26,250
- [giggling]

107
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,500
<i>- Wait a sec.</i>

108
00:07:28,583 --> 00:07:32,083
<i>in a waltz,</i>

109
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:35,041
<i>the melody shifts</i>
<i>to the bottom part.</i>

110
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:36,750
<i>- No, you don't!</i>

111
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:37,708
<i>If you think you're off</i>
<i>the hook,</i>

112
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,333
<i>you couldn't be more wrong!</i>

113
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:42,875
<i>I've got you in my clutches,</i>
<i>Arima!</i>

114
00:07:42,958 --> 00:07:45,750
<i>Two months ago I'd be</i>
<i>sitting here in tears.</i>

115
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:48,791
<i>All that practice,</i>
<i>it's paying off.</i>

116
00:07:48,875 --> 00:07:52,500
<i>Every moment I spend</i>
<i>at the piano led to this.</i>

117
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:58,791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

118
00:07:58,875 --> 00:08:00,666
<i>- Arima's got a heart</i>
<i>of steel!</i>

119
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:02,458
<i>It's like he's a robot!</i>

120
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:04,458
<i>Nothing even touches the guy!</i>

121
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:06,250
<i>- You're wrong.</i>

122
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:07,333
<i>Arima's no robot,</i>

123
00:08:07,416 --> 00:08:08,958
<i>and his heart isn't made</i>
<i>of steel.</i>

124
00:08:09,041 --> 00:08:12,625
<i>It's fragile</i>
<i>like anyone else's.</i>

125
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:14,125
<i>I know.</i>

126
00:08:14,208 --> 00:08:16,958
<i>His hands were warm</i>
<i>when they held mine.</i>

127
00:08:17,041 --> 00:08:19,166
<i>Something in that moment</i>
<i>reminded me</i>

128
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:21,500
<i>of all the time</i>
<i>we've spent together.</i>

129
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:25,666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

130
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:28,000
<i>- What Arima's doing</i>
<i>is perfect.</i>

131
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:31,125
<i>He knows her talents</i>
<i>and her weak points.</i>

132
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:34,833
<i>He plays to both,</i>
<i>forcing her to adapt,</i>

133
00:08:34,916 --> 00:08:36,041
<i>and under such adversity,</i>

134
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:39,250
<i>She's growing</i>
<i>like never before.</i>

135
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:40,500
<i>- That sweet potato</i>
<i>he brought me,</i>

136
00:08:40,583 --> 00:08:43,000
<i>it was so good.</i>

137
00:08:43,083 --> 00:08:45,541
<i>And those pork buns we bought</i>
<i>on the way home,</i>

138
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:47,333
<i>they were delicious.</i>

139
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:49,333
<i>- This is their waltz,</i>

140
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:50,458
<i>every note of it.</i>

141
00:08:50,541 --> 00:08:54,958
<i>♪ ♪</i>

142
00:08:55,041 --> 00:08:57,333
<i>Nagi: the only reason</i>
<i>I started up with the piano</i>

143
00:08:57,416 --> 00:08:59,458
<i>was to try and get</i>
<i>my brother's attention,</i>

144
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:01,500
<i>not for the music.</i>

145
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:04,333
<i>Takeshi,</i>
<i>these last few weeks,</i>

146
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:06,166
<i>I've been peering into</i>
<i>the abyss.</i>

147
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:07,750
<i>just a little, but still.</i>

148
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,291
<i>I cried till I threw up.</i>

149
00:09:09,375 --> 00:09:13,375
<i>I went without food or sleep</i>
<i>just to give it my all.</i>

150
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:15,208
<i>looking myself in the eye</i>
<i>day after day,</i>

151
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:19,750
<i>knowing I wasn't good enough,</i>
<i>it hurt so much.</i>

152
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,458
<i>I bet you felt the same way.</i>

153
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:24,250
<i>- Playing for the sake</i>
<i>of another person</i>

154
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:26,708
<i>makes all the difference</i>
<i>in the world.</i>

155
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:28,083
<i>- Maybe so,</i>

156
00:09:28,166 --> 00:09:29,708
<i>but that's not what</i>
<i>I want for you.</i>

157
00:09:29,791 --> 00:09:31,000
- [gasps]

158
00:09:31,083 --> 00:09:32,833
<i>- Keep fighting every day</i>
<i>twice as hard.</i>

159
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:35,125
<i>Give it your all, brother!</i>

160
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:36,875
<i>Your all and then some!</i>

161
00:09:36,958 --> 00:09:39,000
<i>You've never been one</i>
<i>to lose your way.</i>

162
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:41,041
<i>Take those stairs like</i>
<i>they're nothing at all.</i>

163
00:09:41,125 --> 00:09:43,208
<i>Take them two or three</i>
<i>at a time.</i>

164
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,250
<i>Let me chase you again,</i>

165
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:47,000
<i>just like I did</i>
<i>in the old days.</i>

166
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:49,166
<i>Be my hero again!</i>

167
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:56,208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

168
00:10:05,916 --> 00:10:07,208
<i>- Uh-huh.</i>

169
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:10,208
<i>I'm sure those two would</i>
<i>rather die than admit it,</i>

170
00:10:10,291 --> 00:10:13,416
<i>but they share a lot more</i>
<i>in common than they don't.</i>

171
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,333
<i>Right, Kousei?</i>

172
00:10:15,416 --> 00:10:17,250
<i>- I'm not like</i>
<i>the rest of you.</i>

173
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:18,916
<i>I don't wanna go pro.</i>

174
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:22,083
<i>I'm not ready to dedicate</i>
<i>my whole life to music,</i>

175
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:24,250
<i>but that doesn't mean</i>
<i>no one's listening.</i>

176
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:26,625
<i>There are people</i>
<i>I wanna play for.</i>

177
00:10:26,708 --> 00:10:29,000
<i>People who mean everything</i>
<i>to me,</i>

178
00:10:29,083 --> 00:10:31,458
<i>and so I wanna be here.</i>

179
00:10:31,541 --> 00:10:33,291
<i>Is that selfish of me?</i>

180
00:10:33,375 --> 00:10:34,583
<i>It's a good enough reason</i>

181
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:37,333
<i>for right this second,</i>
<i>isn't it?</i>

182
00:10:37,416 --> 00:10:39,458
<i>- What am I doing</i>
<i>in the audience?</i>

183
00:10:39,541 --> 00:10:43,125
<i>sitting up here in the dark,</i>
<i>watching Arima?</i>

184
00:10:43,208 --> 00:10:46,541
<i>Watching as they dazzle</i>
<i>everyone within earshot.</i>

185
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:49,708
<i>Emi, Nagi,</i>
<i>when you play,</i>

186
00:10:49,791 --> 00:10:52,250
<i>how come it moves people</i>
<i>like it does?</i>

187
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:53,458
<i>Even you!</i>

188
00:10:53,541 --> 00:10:57,583
<i>- Almost done.</i>
<i>It's a weird feeling.</i>

189
00:10:57,666 --> 00:11:02,125
<i>I'm so exhausted but I just</i>
<i>wanna play till I pass out.</i>

190
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:04,625
<i>I wonder if I played</i>
<i>my part right.</i>

191
00:11:04,708 --> 00:11:06,666
<i>Did I face the music</i>
<i>with sincerity?</i>

192
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:14,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

193
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:20,875
<i>Hey, Arima,</i>
<i>tell me.</i>

194
00:11:20,958 --> 00:11:24,166
<i>Why do the sounds you make</i>
<i>echo so beautifully in my head</i>

195
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,916
<i>and my heart?</i>

196
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,291
<i>Even now I feel like</i>
<i>I'm gonna cry.</i>

197
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:33,958
- [breathing heavily]

198
00:11:42,541 --> 00:11:44,541
- [breathing heavily]

199
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:48,583
[whimpering]

200
00:11:52,291 --> 00:11:54,583
- Well, wanna bow?
- Oh, yeah.

201
00:11:54,666 --> 00:11:57,041
<i>- Here it is,</i>

202
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:59,041
<i>after all the weeks</i>
<i>of suffering...</i>

203
00:11:59,125 --> 00:12:01,666
[applause]

204
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:04,208
<i>After plumbing</i>
<i>the depths of your soul...</i>

205
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:05,000
- Amazing!
- Bravo!

206
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:06,541
- Marry me!
- Yeah!

207
00:12:06,625 --> 00:12:08,791
- Nagi!

208
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:11,375
<i>- You're left</i>
<i>with something beautiful.</i>

209
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:14,583
<i>- That's the moment when music</i>
<i>goes deeper than words.</i>

210
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:16,541
- [sniffling]

211
00:12:16,625 --> 00:12:19,958
Hey Arima,
do you think it reached him?

212
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:21,375
- Yeah, it reached him.

213
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:23,875
No doubt.

214
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:27,041
[both cheering]

215
00:12:27,125 --> 00:12:29,666
- What about you, Arima?
- Hmm?

216
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:32,208
- Were you able to kick
your friend in the butt?

217
00:12:32,291 --> 00:12:35,500
- Mm-hmm.
Think so.

218
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:37,833
<i>This was pretty unforgettable.</i>

219
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:40,291
[chuckles]

220
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:42,000
Hmm?

221
00:12:42,083 --> 00:12:44,791
- Huh?
- What the what?

222
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:46,583
- [giggles]

223
00:12:46,666 --> 00:12:47,625
<i>I'm not the phantom after all.</i>

224
00:12:47,708 --> 00:12:49,875
<i>I'm Christine,</i>

225
00:12:49,958 --> 00:12:52,750
<i>and I just debuted</i>
<i>at the opera house.</i>

226
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:58,583
- Your move, Takeshi.

227
00:12:58,666 --> 00:12:59,750
Whatcha gonna do?

228
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:01,083
All these years of putting you
on a pedestal,

229
00:13:01,166 --> 00:13:03,416
and now she turns in
a performance

230
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:05,666
like that with Arima.

231
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:08,375
It might be time for big bro
to take a cue from her

232
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:09,375
and get over it.

233
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:10,416
- Give it a rest.

234
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:11,416
- She gave the performance
of her life.

235
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,958
Doesn't that say anything
to you?

236
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:15,958
- [grunts]

237
00:13:16,041 --> 00:13:18,666
- Of course you could
just sit here.

238
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,916
- We did it!
Yay!

239
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,291
[sighs]

240
00:13:22,375 --> 00:13:23,583
[cheers and applause]

241
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:26,458
- That duet was so incredible,
Nagi.

242
00:13:26,541 --> 00:13:28,750
- Nagi!
- [whimpers]

243
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:31,833
[both speaking at once]

244
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:33,375
- Uh, you guys,
you okay?

245
00:13:33,458 --> 00:13:36,958
<i>It was amazing,</i>
<i>but not 'cause of me.</i>

246
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:39,208
[chuckles]

247
00:13:39,291 --> 00:13:40,125
- [grunts]

248
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:41,875
- savor this moment, teach.

249
00:13:41,958 --> 00:13:43,166
- Hiroko?

250
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:45,041
- This is what it's all about,
you know?

251
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:45,958
- Huh?

252
00:13:46,041 --> 00:13:46,708
What's that supposed to mean?

253
00:13:46,791 --> 00:13:48,583
- [chuckles]

254
00:13:48,666 --> 00:13:50,166
Nothing like it,

255
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:53,250
watching someone spread
their wings.

256
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,625
- I get it.

257
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:59,708
<i>I finally understand why you</i>
<i>put Nagi under my wing.</i>

258
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:01,833
- Ms. Seto!

259
00:14:01,916 --> 00:14:03,250
Did you like our duet?

260
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:05,666
- [grunts]

261
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:08,958
Honestly, ever since you guys
started coming over,

262
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:10,666
life has been a hell
of a lot more colorful.

263
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:13,500
- [grunts]

264
00:14:13,583 --> 00:14:16,416
- [giggles]

265
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:19,083
- Hey, Arima!
- Uh, hold on.

266
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:22,000
You're that guy Takeda, right?

267
00:14:22,083 --> 00:14:23,875
- It's Takeshi!
Ta-ke-shi!

268
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:25,625
- Stop poking me!

269
00:14:25,708 --> 00:14:26,916
- Listen up!

270
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,458
If you lay one finger
on my kid sis,

271
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:29,708
you're going down!

272
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:31,833
- Your kid sis?

273
00:14:31,916 --> 00:14:33,541
- Introduction time.

274
00:14:33,625 --> 00:14:36,583
Meet my big brother Takeshi.
- Huh?

275
00:14:36,666 --> 00:14:37,791
But you said your last name
was Aizato.

276
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:39,875
- That's silly.

277
00:14:39,958 --> 00:14:42,250
Who flubs their own name
meeting Hiroko Seto?

278
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:45,041
I'm Nagi Aiza, see?

279
00:14:45,125 --> 00:14:46,625
You remember that,
don't you?

280
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:47,416
- That's what I heard.

281
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:50,916
- I heard it.
- Hmm.

282
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Well then, guess I'm
the only one who got it wrong.

283
00:14:54,083 --> 00:14:55,625
<i>- Thanks for being</i>
<i>so gullible.</i>

284
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:57,458
- So, why the hell were you
playing a duet with her?

285
00:14:57,541 --> 00:14:59,208
That's what I wanna know,
you sleaze ball!

286
00:14:59,291 --> 00:15:01,125
- I asked if she minded me
teaming up with her!

287
00:15:01,208 --> 00:15:03,625
- Teaming up with
my little sister?

288
00:15:03,708 --> 00:15:05,083
You think I don't know exactly
what that means?

289
00:15:05,166 --> 00:15:08,041
I'm onto you,
you four-eyed horn dog!

290
00:15:08,125 --> 00:15:10,083
- Can I please go home now?

291
00:15:10,166 --> 00:15:11,958
- Stop it, Takeshi.
You're being a butt.

292
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:12,916
- What the hell?

293
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,791
Are you defending
this cradle-robber?

294
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:15,583
How'd you even get mixed up
with Arima, anyway?

295
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:17,708
Tell me!

296
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,583
- I met him a couple
of months ago.

297
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:20,375
You wouldn't believe
all the stuff

298
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:21,750
he's taught me how to do.

299
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:23,083
- Taught you how to do?!

300
00:15:23,166 --> 00:15:25,541
- Thanks to him I'm way more
experienced than I used to be.

301
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:27,208
- Experienced?!

302
00:15:27,708 --> 00:15:31,125
[crying]

303
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:32,958
- Takeshi!

304
00:15:33,041 --> 00:15:34,583
- [grunts]
- [whimpers]

305
00:15:34,666 --> 00:15:36,250
- Watch your back, man,

306
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:38,416
'cause the eastern Japan piano
competition is coming.

307
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:41,583
I'm gonna kick your ass up
and down the stage

308
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:42,083
for everyone to see!

309
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:44,291
- [grunts]

310
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:45,416
<i>- Takeshi.</i>

311
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:46,750
[door opens]

312
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:50,041
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

313
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:51,875
[gasps]

314
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:53,000
<i>- Bring it on, Arima.</i>

315
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:54,916
<i>I dare you.</i>

316
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,458
<i>Playing a duet with my sister.</i>

317
00:15:56,541 --> 00:15:58,791
<i>You've got a lot of nerve.</i>

318
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:04,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

319
00:16:04,541 --> 00:16:06,083
- There you have it.

320
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:09,291
Nothing but musical drama
through to the end of the year.

321
00:16:09,375 --> 00:16:12,041
<i>- A tenth of my feelings,</i>

322
00:16:12,125 --> 00:16:14,291
<i>even just 100th,</i>

323
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:16,791
<i>did any of it get through</i>
<i>to him?</i>

324
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:20,791
<i>Was my music enough</i>
<i>to carry them?</i>

325
00:16:20,875 --> 00:16:22,958
[gasps]

326
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:25,041
- You really shined out there.

327
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:28,083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

328
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:30,666
- Thank you so much, Arima.

329
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:31,708
Thank you.

330
00:16:31,791 --> 00:16:34,375
[crying]

331
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,750
<i>- Uh, hey, Aiza!</i>

332
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:45,833
all: Hmm?

333
00:16:45,916 --> 00:16:48,416
- Miike?

334
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,041
<i>What's this about?</i>

335
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:52,458
<i>The guy's never acknowledged</i>
<i>my existence before,</i>

336
00:16:52,541 --> 00:16:54,958
<i>and now he just yells out</i>
<i>my name?</i>

337
00:16:55,041 --> 00:16:56,291
- Tell me something, Aiza.

338
00:16:56,375 --> 00:16:59,833
How come you were playing
a duet with Kousei Arima

339
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:01,125
of all people?

340
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:03,500
Is Kousei, like, a personal
friend of yours or what?

341
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:06,791
- Did you just
call him Kousei?!

342
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:07,791
Bite your tongue!

343
00:17:07,875 --> 00:17:08,333
How dare you call him by his
first name,

344
00:17:08,416 --> 00:17:09,833
you little twerp?

345
00:17:09,916 --> 00:17:10,750
That's Arima to you!
Mr. Arima!

346
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:12,750
- Mr.?

347
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:13,958
He's, like, two years
older than us.

348
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:14,791
Why would I call him that?

349
00:17:14,875 --> 00:17:16,166
You don't mean to tell me that

350
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:17,833
you got his phone number,
right?

351
00:17:17,916 --> 00:17:19,583
- In my cell and everything.

352
00:17:19,666 --> 00:17:21,125
We even stopped
for some taiyaki

353
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:22,416
on the way home yesterday.

354
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:24,916
Just him and me all alone.

355
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,583
- Nagi has his phone number?

356
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:30,541
<i>They ate taiyaki</i>
<i>just the two of them?</i>

357
00:17:30,625 --> 00:17:31,958
<i>Why?</i>

358
00:17:32,041 --> 00:17:33,041
I can't believe you get
to be his friend!

359
00:17:33,125 --> 00:17:35,291
That is so unfair!

360
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:37,041
[crying]

361
00:17:37,125 --> 00:17:39,541
- What was that about?

362
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:46,333
- ♪ Twinkle, twinkle
little star ♪

363
00:17:46,416 --> 00:17:51,416
♪ How I wonder what you are ♪

364
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:52,375
[laughing]

365
00:17:52,458 --> 00:17:53,458
I keep messing up that part.

366
00:17:55,708 --> 00:18:00,375
♪ Twinkle, twinkle
little star ♪

367
00:18:00,458 --> 00:18:04,875
♪ How I wonder what you are ♪

368
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:09,583
♪ Up above the world so high ♪

369
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:14,583
♪ Like a diamond in the sky ♪

370
00:18:14,666 --> 00:18:17,958
♪ Twinkle, twinkle li... ♪

371
00:18:19,125 --> 00:18:22,166
Hey.
- Hey.

372
00:18:22,250 --> 00:18:24,416
- Is this guy your boyfriend,
Kaori?

373
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,250
- Boyfriend?
- Hmm?

374
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:28,208
No, he's not my boyfriend.

375
00:18:28,291 --> 00:18:30,625
What this guy here is,
is a jackass!

376
00:18:30,708 --> 00:18:31,583
- A jackass?
- Jackass!

377
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:33,625
- Huh?
That's totally unfair!

378
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:35,416
- What word would you use?

379
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,458
<i>[piano music playing]</i>

380
00:18:37,541 --> 00:18:41,083
You take a violinist
who can't even play

381
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,666
and make her listen
to this song?

382
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:45,958
<i>I didn't miss it before,</i>
<i>but now...</i>

383
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,416
[phone beeps]

384
00:18:51,541 --> 00:18:55,041
- I can't kill myself with you.

385
00:18:55,125 --> 00:18:56,916
- I figured as much.

386
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,458
- Think about it.

387
00:18:58,541 --> 00:18:59,708
When we went shopping,

388
00:18:59,791 --> 00:19:01,291
you led the way the whole time.

389
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:06,125
I just followed you with all
those bags of cute stuff.

390
00:19:06,208 --> 00:19:09,291
You're always five steps ahead
of me,

391
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:12,291
and I'm always bringing up
the rear.

392
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:13,791
<i>Every time I think of you,</i>

393
00:19:13,875 --> 00:19:17,541
<i>you're slipping farther into</i>
<i>the distance.</i>

394
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:20,166
Technically speaking,
if we died,

395
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:22,166
it wouldn't be together.

396
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:26,000
I'd be following you,
just like always.

397
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:28,500
I want another chance
to stand by your side.

398
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:32,458
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

399
00:19:32,541 --> 00:19:35,208
So please,
play with me one more time.

400
00:19:35,291 --> 00:19:39,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

401
00:19:39,541 --> 00:19:42,291
- But I--I can't
even hold the bow.

402
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:44,791
- You don't have
to be the princess.

403
00:19:44,875 --> 00:19:47,833
You're a girl in middle school
who has a sweet tooth,

404
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:51,041
not some tragic heroine,

405
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:55,083
and I won't play Ravel.
Not ever again.

406
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:58,000
One more duet.
That's all I ask.

407
00:19:59,916 --> 00:20:01,541
As a good friend once said,

408
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:04,208
"Do you think
you can just forget?"

409
00:20:04,291 --> 00:20:08,000
[cheers and applause]

410
00:20:08,083 --> 00:20:12,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

411
00:20:12,791 --> 00:20:14,375
- You're cruel.

412
00:20:14,458 --> 00:20:17,583
You know that, right?

413
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:19,625
- I wouldn't say cruel.

414
00:20:19,708 --> 00:20:23,000
I'm more of a jackass.

415
00:20:23,083 --> 00:20:26,708
<i>- The air is chilly</i>
<i>and dry as the fallen leaves.</i>

416
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:32,041
<i>The laundered sheets dance</i>
<i>to the rhythm of the wind.</i>

417
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:35,958
<i>You really are cruel</i>
<i>to come here like this</i>

418
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:37,375
<i>and speak of dreams.</i>

419
00:20:37,458 --> 00:20:42,375
<i>My dream came true,</i>
<i>and that was enough for me,</i>

420
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:44,583
<i>or so I thought,</i>

421
00:20:44,666 --> 00:20:46,291
<i>but here you are,</i>

422
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:50,083
<i>watering my withered heart</i>
<i>with your smile.</i>

423
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:52,666
<i>- Hey!</i>

424
00:20:52,750 --> 00:20:54,375
Stop it!
Don't make her cry!

425
00:20:54,458 --> 00:20:56,833
- That's why you're a jackass!
- No, no, no, no!

426
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:57,791
I'm not being mean!
I swear!

427
00:20:57,875 --> 00:21:00,208
Please stop hitting me!
Help!

428
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:02,375
- [laughing]

429
00:21:02,458 --> 00:21:04,375
<i>Maybe I'm just greedy,</i>

430
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:06,250
<i>but I wanna dream again.</i>

431
00:21:06,333 --> 00:21:12,416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

432
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:17,625
<i>Someday we'll waltz together.</i>

433
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:18,958
<i>We just might.</i>

434
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:23,500
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

435
00:21:23,583 --> 00:21:26,500
<i>[7!!'s "Orange"]</i>

436
00:21:26,583 --> 00:21:32,791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

437
00:21:54,958 --> 00:22:01,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

438
00:22:16,291 --> 00:22:23,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

